<div class="container">
    <div class="text-center">
        <img src="~/images/logo.png" alt="Task Planner" />
        <h2 id="homePageContent">
            Task Planner
        </h2>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1" id="textContent">
                <p style="margin-top:15px;line-height:40px;font-size:20px!important" class="secondary-color">A simple easy-to-use standalone application to plan project road maps, user stories, and backlogs, estimates effortlessly using the appealing and user friendly interface for software development.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        @*<a class="btn btn-primary" id="getStarted" href="https://github.com/bharatdwarkani/taskplanner" target="_blank">Project Source (GitHub)</a>*@
        <a class="btn btn-primary" id="getStarted" href="/showcase/aspnetcore/task-planner/project">Get Started</a>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="container-fluid bg-color" style="background: aliceblue;">
    <div class="container-fluid">
        <div class="row homeDescription">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <img class="homeImage" src="http://www.syncfusion.com/downloads/support/directtrac/general/yours_big1026177797.png">
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <div class="titleContent">
                    <h3>What this application does?</h3>
                </div>
                <ul style="margin-top:20px;margin-bottom:30px;margin-left:-20px">
                    <li>Reduces efforts in writing stories.</li>
                    <li>Creates stories in seconds using the actual issue tracker.</li>
                    <li>Prepares roadmaps for projects.</li>
                    <li>Prioritizes and filters the stories.</li>
                    <li>Groups the stories by themes, epics, release, and sprints.</li>
                    <li>Prepares and shares the estimates to customers.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>


<div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row homeDescription">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="titleContent">
                <h3>Creating new project</h3>
            </div>
            <ul style="margin-top:20px;margin-bottom:30px;margin-left:-20px">
                <li>Use the add project option to create a project.</li>
                <li>Add a title and description; your project will be created in no time.</li>
                <li>Initially, this project is visible only to the creator but it can be shared to others.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <img class="homeImage" src="http://www.syncfusion.com/downloads/support/directtrac/general/add_project_small-692253460.png">
        </div>
    </div>
</div>


<div class="container-fluid" style="background: aliceblue;">
    <div class="container-fluid">
        <div class="row homeDescription">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <img class="homeImage" src="http://www.syncfusion.com/downloads/support/directtrac/general/share-1721313206.png">
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <div class="titleContent">
                    <h3>Sharing Project</h3>
                </div>
                <ul style="margin-top:20px;margin-bottom:30px;margin-left:-20px">
                    <li>Use the share icon to open the permission dialog.</li>
                    <li>Add a Gmail ID of user to whom you want to share a project.</li>
                    <li>Copy the project link and share to the user.</li>
                    <li>Shared user can work collaboratively in planning stories.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row homeDescription">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="titleContent">
                <h3>Writing Stories</h3>
            </div>
            <ul style="margin-top:20px;margin-bottom:30px;margin-left:-20px">
                <li>Go to the project story plan page by clicking the project name.</li>
                <li>Use the add option to write stories.</li>
                <li>Title is only mandatory and other fields are optional.</li>
            </ul>

        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <img class="homeImage" src="http://www.syncfusion.com/downloads/support/directtrac/general/stories_large-1402687599.png">
        </div>
    </div>
</div>


<div class="container-fluid" style="background: aliceblue;">
    <div class="container-fluid">
        <div class="row homeDescription">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <img class="homeImage" src="http://www.syncfusion.com/downloads/support/directtrac/general/groupby-2072987122.png">
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <div class="titleContent">
                    <h3>Group by themes, epic</h3>
                </div>
                <ul style="margin-top:20px;margin-bottom:30px;margin-left:-20px">
                    <li>Fill an epic and theme fields in stories.</li>
                    <li>Now, drag and drop a column which you want to group in the drop area.</li>
                    <li>Now, the stories are grouped by epics or themes.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>


<div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row homeDescription">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="titleContent">
                <h3>Add estimates, penalty, benefit and priority</h3>
            </div>
            <ul style="margin-top:20px;margin-bottom:30px;margin-left:-20px">
                <li>Fill the estimate, penalty, and benefit column in grid.</li> 
                <li>Users can sort/filter the features using the penalty or benefit field.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <img class="homeImage" src="http://www.syncfusion.com/downloads/support/directtrac/general/estimate1791029700.png">
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container-fluid" style="background: aliceblue;">
    <div class="container-fluid homeDescription">
        <div class="row homeDescription">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <img class="homeImage" src="http://www.syncfusion.com/downloads/support/directtrac/general/planfor_release-1064830497.png">
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <div class="titleContent">
                    <h3>Plan for release or sprint</h3>
                </div>
                <ul style="margin-top:20px;margin-bottom:30px;margin-left:-20px">
                    <li>Sprint and release fields that are hidden under the column chooser when filled, this feature can be utilized.</li>
                    <li>The filled stories can be grouped and sorted by these fields.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row homeDescription">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="titleContent">
                <h3>Including more fields</h3>

            </div>
            <ul style="margin-top:20px;margin-bottom:30px;margin-left:-20px">
                <li>Fields such as status, sprint, release, and assignee are hidden in the column chooser.</li>
                <li>Those fields can also be utilized based on project needs.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <img class="homeImage" src="http://www.syncfusion.com/downloads/support/directtrac/general/columnchooser574762085.png">
        </div>
    </div>
</div>


<div class="container-fluid" style="background-color:bisque">
    <div class="text-center">
        <h3 id="homePageContent">Use Cases</h3>
    </div>
    <ul style="margin-top:20px;margin-bottom:30px">
        <li>Start-up companies can use this to prepare a roadmap for their products.</li>
        <li>Consulting companies can use this to prepare a plan, estimate cost or hour for requirements, and share them to customer.</li>
        <li>Freelancers or small teams can use this to prepare a list of features for their product.</li>
        <li>Product Owners/Scrum master can use this to create a plan for their product release or sprints.</li>
        <li>Product Owners/Scrum master can use this to prepare and share roadmaps.</li>
        <li>As it provides an organized plan for story writing, it can be used effortlessly as a replacement for document editors/Excel sheets.</li>
        <li>There are several fields which can be used in different ways either for preparing roadmaps, sprint plan, release plan, or preparing estimates.</li>
        <li>Stories can be exported to Excel.</li>
        <li>Stories can be grouped or sorted by themes, epics, estimation, assignee, sprint, or release easily..</li>
        <li>Estimate, penalty, benefit, and  priority can also be set for stories.</li>
        <li>Reduces the product owner’s time and effort to write stories as they are not writing stories in the actual issue tracker; it takes time for a single-story creation, which can be then passed on written stories to scrum masters to convert it to actual tasks with detailed requirement in the issue tracker.</li>
        <li>It can be used as an initial stage tool in the software development lifecycle for filtering features and setting priority.</li>
        <li>It can also be used as an application to create checklists. Share testing plan to testing engineers.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

 


